.TH "comedi_isadma_alloc" 9 "comedi_isadma_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
comedi_isadma_alloc \- allocate and initialize the ISA DMA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct comedi_isadma *" comedi_isadma_alloc
.BI "(struct comedi_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int n_desc "  ","
.BI "unsigned int dma_chan1 "  ","
.BI "unsigned int dma_chan2 "  ","
.BI "unsigned int maxsize "  ","
.BI "char dma_dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
comedi_device struct
.IP "n_desc" 12
the number of cookies to allocate
.IP "dma_chan1" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "dma_chan2" 12
DMA channel for the second cookie
.IP "maxsize" 12
the size of the buffer to allocate for each cookie
.IP "dma_dir" 12
the DMA direction
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the allocated and initialized ISA DMA or NULL if anything fails.
